Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.19,0:00:20.39,Default - flashback,Chief,0000,0000,0000,,To us of the demon clan, twins are taboo.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.48,0:00:23.41,Default - flashback,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Please wait, Chief!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.41,0:00:27.40,Default - flashback,Chief,0000,0000,0000,,No! To protect our pride as a race,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.40,0:00:28.75,Default - flashback,Chief,0000,0000,0000,,we must dispose of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.57,0:00:31.46,Default - flashback,Chief,0000,0000,0000,,Such is the demon clan's custom!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.00,0:00:33.29,Default - flashback,Chief,0000,0000,0000,,It is our law!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.60,0:01:04.91,Default - flashback,Chief,0000,0000,0000,,This child is...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.44,0:01:32.53,Default - flashback,Chief,0000,0000,0000,,She is a true prodigy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.03,0:01:35.78,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Such power, with only one horn!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.78,0:01:38.70,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,If she'd had two horns...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.76,0:01:43.58,Default - flashback,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,Very good, Ram...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.58,0:01:45.91,Default - flashback,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Rem, follow your sister's \Nexample and work hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.51,0:01:47.67,Default - flashback,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.67,0:01:51.03,Default - flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,One day, Rem will show us that \Nshe has incredible power.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.03,0:01:54.42,Default - flashback,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,You're right. She is Ram's sister, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.94,0:01:56.41,Default - flashback,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,We expect great things.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.41,0:02:17.57,Default - flashback,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.67,0:02:21.23,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Sissy...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.23,0:02:22.37,Default - flashback,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,Just be you, Rem.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.98,0:02:25.83,Default - flashback,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to worry about what people say.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.02,0:02:48.97,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I can never match my sister in demon power.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.69,0:02:50.31,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.80,0:03:00.52,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.51,0:03:03.28,Default - flashback,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Rem?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.58,0:03:06.49,Default - flashback,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,I'll make dinner tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.88,0:03:11.16,Default - flashback,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,What are you making for dinner?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.16,0:03:12.27,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.27,0:03:16.56,Default - flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe a stir-fry with barbaro rabbit \Nmeat and nuts from the forest trees.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.56,0:03:18.46,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,And steamed tatoes!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.46,0:03:20.00,Default - flashback,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,I'll help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.00,0:03:23.28,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'll be fine by myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.28,0:03:24.39,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Just watch me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.75,0:03:34.82,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Now, I just need a barbaro rabbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.93,0:04:06.14,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Sissy!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.42,0:04:16.73,Default - flashback,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just so glad you're both all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.92,0:04:19.44,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Both...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.83,0:04:23.04,Default - flashback,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,Rem, don't go into the forest alone again.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.04,0:04:24.82,Default - flashback,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,You don't want to worry your sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.47,0:04:28.07,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.49,0:04:31.86,Default - flashback,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, don't forget about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.73,0:04:36.78,Default - flashback,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,The steamed tatoes Rem made are really good.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.49,0:04:39.13,Default - flashback,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,They have just the right amount of salt.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.71,0:04:42.13,Default - flashback,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,You're right! They are good!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.75,0:04:45.78,Default - flashback,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,I had no idea Rem could make \Nsomething so delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.84,0:04:59.90,Default - flashback,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough, Rem.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.57,0:05:04.36,Default - flashback,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just happy both of you are all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.36,0:05:06.99,Default - flashback,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, we're so glad you're both safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.23,0:05:12.08,Default - flashback,Chief,0000,0000,0000,,No, it would have been better \Nif only Ram had been safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.08,0:05:13.69,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.69,0:05:14.75,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,You said it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.72,0:05:19.88,Default - flashback,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, if only that useless Rem had died...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.88,0:05:22.80,Default - flashback,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,It would have been best if only Ram had lived.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.17,0:05:47.24,Default - flashback,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,You were having a scary dream, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.72,0:05:49.30,Default - flashback,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,You were moaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.94,0:05:51.53,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Sissy...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.53,0:05:54.23,Default - flashback,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right. I'm with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.76,0:05:57.25,Default - flashback,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,So you don't have to worry about anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.30,0:06:00.33,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Sissy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.97,0:06:03.14,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,I love you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.46,0:06:07.83,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My sister really is amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.83,0:06:09.64,Default - flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I can't match her in anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.17,0:06:13.26,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In that case, I don't have\N to do anything anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.01,0:06:17.14,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I can just walk behind her.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.28,0:06:27.85,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Sissy?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.19,0:07:03.06,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Sissy!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.90,0:07:16.49,Default - flashback,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,Rem... I'm glad you're safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.47,0:07:35.81,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It finally broke off.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.79,0:07:39.48,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Because of me,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.96,0:07:41.69,Default - flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}my sister's horn was broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.39,0:07:44.15,Default - flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And she lost her power.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.82,0:07:48.57,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}From now on, I have to learn to \Ndo all the things that Sissy...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.92,0:07:51.45,Default - flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That Sister could do.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.95,0:07:53.41,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This is what Sister would have done.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.99,0:07:55.32,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sister is far more amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.85,0:07:57.66,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sister could do even more.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.00,0:08:00.62,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I only imitate what Sister could do.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.99,0:08:03.08,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If I cannot even do that satisfactorily,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.96,0:08:05.50,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I am worthless.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.89,0:08:08.08,Default - flashback,Roswaal,0000,0000,0000,,You're doing a fine job...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.08,0:08:11.47,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Many times, I heard those words back home.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.89,0:08:14.47,Default - flashback,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,Don't overdo it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.47,0:08:17.43,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even if I overdo everything, \Nit will never be enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.81,0:08:20.14,Default - flashback,Frederica,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you try so hard?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.44,0:08:24.02,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Why else? Because nothing I do is enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.43,0:08:26.56,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Why should I go on living?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.56,0:08:30.44,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}All of this is my atonement for
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.75,0:08:32.95,Default - flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}what I thought on that fiery night.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.65,0:08:35.91,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What can I do to atone?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.18,0:08:40.28,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I shall risk my life to walk the path \Nthat Sister would have walked,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.28,0:08:42.45,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the path I took from her.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.04,0:08:47.04,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Because I am inferior to her in every way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.04,0:08:49.67,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I am nothing but a replacement.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.84,0:08:55.31,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,Barusu, head to the right of \Nthat broken tree ahead!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.31,0:08:56.20,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,You're too slow!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.20,0:08:57.59,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Don't ask any more of me...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.08,0:09:00.35,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I'm running... as fast as I can!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.88,0:09:04.00,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Subaru-kun... What...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.00,0:09:05.23,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You're awake, Rem?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.06,0:09:09.19,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,Thank goodness, Rem. \NYou really are a handful.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.44,0:09:12.25,Default - italics,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,Fula!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.89,0:09:22.40,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Why...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.32,0:09:27.02,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you just leave me alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.80,0:09:31.83,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,For you and Sister to show up \Nmakes it all pointless.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.42,0:09:34.56,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,I have to do it by myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.56,0:09:36.97,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,No one else needs to get hurt anymore...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.97,0:09:38.67,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Too late for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.67,0:09:41.60,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Ram and I are already torn to shreds, \Nmaybe even more than you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.96,0:09:44.30,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,My right shoulder's dislocated!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.22,0:09:48.73,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,It's... It's my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.73,0:09:51.64,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,So I have to take responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.64,0:09:56.07,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,If I don't, I cannot do anything \Nfor Sister or you...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.27,0:10:00.34,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't changed at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.12,0:10:04.37,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,I committed the same sin \Nas I did back then!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.37,0:10:09.06,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Because I hesitated to \Nextend my hand to you...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.84,0:10:12.17,Default - flashback,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The witch's scent?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.69,0:10:15.17,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,You nearly died.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.40,0:10:20.36,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure what you're talking about,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.36,0:10:24.31,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,but to atone for that, you got mad \Nand decided to do this alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.66,0:10:26.48,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Rem...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.40,0:10:30.44,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.76,0:10:33.02,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Super slap!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.00,0:10:36.44,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,For starters, are you dumb?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.44,0:10:38.38,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,No, you are dumb!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.38,0:10:41.46,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,Barusu, the cut on your forehead \Nhas reopened and is bleeding.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.46,0:10:43.76,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I know I'm dumb, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.76,0:10:46.12,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,But your sister is even dumber!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.56,0:10:50.89,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, where I'm from there's a saying, \N"Three heads are better than one."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.89,0:10:52.32,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, is it two heads?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.32,0:10:53.83,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever... The point is,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.83,0:10:57.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,three heads, thinking together, \Nare harder to break than only one arrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.89,0:10:59.42,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,It means you should rely on
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.42,0:11:01.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,those around you instead of \Nthinking about stuff alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.57,0:11:04.14,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Subaru-kun...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.43,0:11:09.64,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Damn...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.97,0:11:13.00,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Ram, which way should we run \Nto get outside the barrier?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.00,0:11:15.65,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,We'd have to run left, at full \Nspeed. What's your plan?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.06,0:11:22.21,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I could shove Rem toward you and \Nrun tragically to the right—
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.21,0:11:23.78,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,I'll draw the ulgarm's attention,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.78,0:11:25.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,while you take Rem and run.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.30,0:11:28.04,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Could you not expose my attempt at \Nhiding my embarrassment so easily?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.04,0:11:30.66,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way you will survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.66,0:11:34.21,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't. If you do that, I will...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.72,0:11:36.32,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.32,0:11:40.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't know my brilliant plan \Nto round up all the mabeasts.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.84,0:11:44.01,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Subaru-kun, why would you do all this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.76,0:11:46.35,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.23,0:11:53.50,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You were my partner for my very first date.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.27,0:11:56.57,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't be so heartless as to desert you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.48,0:12:03.45,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,All right, guess I'd better go and do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.96,0:12:06.23,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Take care of Rem, Onee-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.23,0:12:08.96,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be praying for our safe reunion, Barusu.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.42,0:12:12.62,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,Barusu's risking his life to buy us time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.04,0:12:14.62,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,Let's make the most of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.76,0:12:26.54,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I'd love to finish you off right about now...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.53,0:12:39.86,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I have an ace up my sleeve, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.07,0:12:43.49,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,It's you and me, pal... Get ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.11,0:12:47.03,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Sister! Subaru-kun is... Subaru-kun is...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.03,0:12:48.77,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,Don't look back, Rem.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.77,0:12:50.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Barusu's determination will be for nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.51,0:13:00.65,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Sissy!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.03,0:13:09.97,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Subaru-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.10,0:13:14.61,Default - italics,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Shamac!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.31,0:13:29.40,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I could do without the bugs, \Nbut I appreciate the bocco fruit!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.40,0:13:31.83,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for that, brats.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.92,0:13:35.08,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Crap—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.78,0:13:43.51,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You need to die!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.84,0:13:49.93,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter? \NBring it on, boss garm!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.06,0:13:53.68,Default - italics,Roswaal,0000,0000,0000,,Ulgoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.91,0:14:05.94,Default,Roswaal,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my! You look an absolute fright!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.84,0:14:11.67,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You're way late, Ros-chi...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.79,0:14:17.84,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm surprised you\N knew where to find me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.84,0:14:22.46,Default,Roswaal,0000,0000,0000,,In the village, Emilia-sama drove \Nit into me quite thoroughly...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.79,0:14:26.02,Default,Roswaal,0000,0000,0000,,"Even if it's rash or reckless, \Nhe'll use magic if he's cornered,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.02,0:14:29.73,Default,Roswaal,0000,0000,0000,,so don't lose sight of \Nhim from above," she said.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.73,0:14:31.55,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,Roswaal-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.14,0:14:39.00,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,I am sorry to cause so\Nmuch trouble for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.00,0:14:41.25,Default,Roswaal,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.25,0:14:45.11,Default,Roswaal,0000,0000,0000,,In fact, you both did fine work in my absence.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.19,0:14:51.06,Default,Roswaal,0000,0000,0000,,I shall most certainly show my \Ngratitude for your actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.53,0:14:52.89,Default,Roswaal,0000,0000,0000,,You have my word.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.93,0:14:55.19,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Subaru-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.70,0:14:58.05,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Rem, that hurts! Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.50,0:15:00.58,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I'm kinda hurt all over right now...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.92,0:15:03.67,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,You're alive... You stayed alive...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.67,0:15:07.24,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Subaru-kun! Subaru-kun! Subaru-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.24,0:15:10.90,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,865)}This... again...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.65,0:15:20.79,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Are you awake?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.38,0:15:32.61,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Did I do this? Like, grabbed you \Nand never let go?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.04,0:15:35.62,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,No, um... This is, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.04,0:15:38.33,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,I did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.86,0:15:43.37,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,While you slept, you looked as \Nif you were in pain, so I...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.06,0:15:45.68,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You held my hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.53,0:15:50.15,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,At times like these, \NI do not know what to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.68,0:15:54.84,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,so I did what would have made me \Nhappiest, were I in your place.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.28,0:15:58.49,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, I'd like to hear the rest... I mean,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.49,0:16:00.14,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to know how it ended.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.76,0:16:03.28,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Were my curses removed?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.28,0:16:07.99,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Roswaal-sama took \Ncare of all the mabeasts.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.54,0:16:11.74,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,So there is no chance \Nthe curses will activate.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.76,0:16:17.83,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,I am sorry, Subaru-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.08,0:16:20.70,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Hey... Come on, lift your head, Rem.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.70,0:16:22.87,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing wrong with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.02,0:16:27.05,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You always look calm,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.05,0:16:30.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but you're not remotely calm \Nor collected, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.20,0:16:33.17,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,I do realize
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.87,0:16:38.73,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,that I am a powerless and \Nincompetent demon clan dropout.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.73,0:16:41.49,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,So no matter what I do, \NI can never match my sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.06,0:16:44.24,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,I am merely her replacement,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.24,0:16:46.45,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,and I have always been inferior.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.45,0:16:47.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good for nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.08,0:16:55.61,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Why was I the one to keep my horn?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.41,0:17:01.07,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Why could Sister not be the one to keep hers?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.07,0:17:06.33,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Why was she born with only one horn?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.75,0:17:10.96,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Why did... we have to be twins?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.57,0:17:17.38,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize. That was a strange \Nthing for me to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.38,0:17:18.82,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Please forget it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.07,0:17:25.80,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You know, Rem, you keep \Nputting Ram on a pedestal
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.80,0:17:27.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and undermining yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.99,0:17:30.23,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,but if she were in your position,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.23,0:17:32.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think she'd be any better off.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.15,0:17:35.81,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Ram is weaker than you, she can't cook,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.81,0:17:38.03,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,slacks off on the job, says mean things.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.03,0:17:39.91,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You're wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.28,0:17:42.20,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Sister's true self is more...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.20,0:17:44.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If she had her horn, you would not say...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.80,0:17:48.08,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,But Ram doesn't have her horn,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.08,0:17:50.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I don't know that Ram.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.72,0:17:52.91,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I'm pretty sure you're the only one
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.91,0:17:56.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who cares whether she has a horn or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.48,0:18:00.06,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,What Ram doesn't have, you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.69,0:18:02.54,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Just accept that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.17,0:18:06.91,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You're kind, hardworking, always do your best,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.91,0:18:09.52,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,and your chest is bigger than hers!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.55,0:18:15.02,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,If you hadn't been around, those dogs \Nwould've chewed me to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.65,0:18:18.45,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I was saved because you were there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.90,0:18:21.23,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,And as you can see, I'm alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.23,0:18:24.75,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Not only because of your sister, \Nbut because of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.86,0:18:28.88,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,My true Sister could have done much more.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.88,0:18:30.96,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe so.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.28,0:18:33.38,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,But you were the one who was there for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.93,0:18:38.02,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad you were there...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.64,0:18:39.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.54,0:18:46.04,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,I... I told you that I am only \Nmy sister's replacement.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.04,0:18:49.31,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Don't define yourself that way. It's too sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.31,0:18:52.76,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, I haven't heard the details \Nof how she lost her horn.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.76,0:18:54.69,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I won't ask, so I'll never know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.06,0:18:58.74,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,And since I don't know, I get to \Ntalk as if I know all about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.12,0:19:04.87,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,All you have to do is be the \Nhorn Ram doesn't have.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.55,0:19:08.86,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You two can be a demon together.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.27,0:19:13.21,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Also, you call yourself a replacement,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.21,0:19:15.62,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,but no one could replace you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.83,0:19:17.80,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.80,0:19:19.49,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Where I come from, there's a saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.49,0:19:23.32,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,"Demons laugh when you talk about next year."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.32,0:19:24.26,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.24,0:19:27.27,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Laugh, Rem.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.27,0:19:30.64,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Take off that sad face, and laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.64,0:19:32.94,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Laugh while we talk about the future!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.96,0:19:37.16,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,While we talk, look forward to making up for
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.16,0:19:40.29,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,all the time you've wasted looking back!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.29,0:19:42.80,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,We can start by talking about tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.80,0:19:44.48,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,Tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.48,0:19:46.88,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Yep, tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.88,0:19:48.63,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,You can say anything, like...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.63,0:19:54.80,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Whether you'll make a Japanese- or \NWestern-style breakfast tomorrow,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.80,0:19:57.90,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,or whether you'll put on your \Nright or left shoe first.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.90,0:19:59.86,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,It can be something silly like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.41,0:20:02.41,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how silly it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.41,0:20:05.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you can talk about tomorrow \Nbecause you {\i1}have{\i0} a tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.47,0:20:06.30,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,How about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.34,0:20:10.84,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,I am... very weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.43,0:20:15.23,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,So I'm sure I will end up leaning on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.23,0:20:16.56,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.25,0:20:21.69,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I'm weak, stupid, scary-looking, and dense.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.14,0:20:27.42,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,But I still live my life, expecting others \Nto take care of things for me...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.07,0:20:31.00,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,As we move forward, we can \Nlean on each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.35,0:20:37.14,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Let's laugh and talk about tomorrow, \Narms around each other's shoulders.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.14,0:20:40.40,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,It's always been my dream to talk \Nabout next year with a demon
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.40,0:20:41.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,while we both laugh!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.97,0:20:46.94,Default,Rem,0000,0000,0000,,You are fanatical like a demon.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.13,0:20:50.06,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.99,0:21:12.79,Episode Title,Title,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1363,1)\fs30}Re{\c&HF9D8B1&}m
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.32,0:21:14.89,Default,Roswaal,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, Ram,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.89,0:21:19.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,did you find the one who was \Ncontrolling the mabeasts?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.56,0:21:22.84,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but the trail has already vanished.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.59,0:21:27.10,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,It seems one of the children that \NBarusu and Rem brought back
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.10,0:21:29.35,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,from the forest disappeared the next day.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.35,0:21:33.02,Default,Roswaal,0000,0000,0000,,Is this going to be another \Nbattle for the throne?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.02,0:21:35.31,Default,Roswaal,0000,0000,0000,,The Bowel Hunter, mabeast masters...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.82,0:21:38.35,Default,Roswaal,0000,0000,0000,,We have involved ourselves with \Nsome bizarre characters.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.84,0:21:41.65,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how many strange \Ncharacters you face,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.65,0:21:43.99,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,you aren't the sort to lose heart, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.36,0:21:47.73,Default,Roswaal,0000,0000,0000,,My, how audacious you have become.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.92,0:21:49.99,Default,Roswaal,0000,0000,0000,,Come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.72,0:21:56.55,Default,Roswaal,0000,0000,0000,,Now, shall we begin?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.03,0:21:59.79,Default,Roswaal,0000,0000,0000,,I was unable to attend to you \Nfor a whole night, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.14,0:22:03.34,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. Please do.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.34,0:22:05.55,Default,Roswaal,0000,0000,0000,,You have used quite a lot of mana.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.51,0:22:08.73,Default,Roswaal,0000,0000,0000,,May the stars protect you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.52,0:22:16.76,Default,Roswaal,0000,0000,0000,,I shall be busy again for a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.76,0:22:20.69,Default,Roswaal,0000,0000,0000,,I know it will be hard on you, \Nbut look after yourself and Rem...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.38,0:22:23.15,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,As you wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.67,0:22:26.35,Default,Ram,0000,0000,0000,,Since that fiery night,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.35,0:22:28.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,my body has belonged to you, Roswaal-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.79,0:22:33.44,Default,Roswaal,0000,0000,0000,,I must win this battle for the throne, \Nno matter what it takes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.44,0:22:35.53,Default,Roswaal,0000,0000,0000,,For the sake of my goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.92,0:22:41.79,Default,Roswaal,0000,0000,0000,,For the coming day when I kill the dragon...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.62,0:22:46.47,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,You're constantly getting hurt, \Naren't you, Subaru?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.47,0:22:50.03,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,You came to this mansion in the \Nfirst place because you were injured.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.03,0:22:53.20,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Since then, it's only been four days.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.20,0:22:56.06,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like I get hurt because I want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.79,0:23:00.80,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,The world's just a little harsh on me...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.80,0:23:04.99,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,So you're welcome to spoil me rotten, \Nsince no one else will, Emilia-tan!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.99,0:23:06.44,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Don't joke around.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.74,0:23:11.04,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Puck kept trying to get me \Nto go after you guys, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.04,0:23:14.15,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows what would've happened \Nif Roswaal hadn't made it back?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.15,0:23:15.21,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Do you get it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.40,0:23:20.52,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Still, I suppose you saved me again.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.52,0:23:21.21,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.52,0:23:25.83,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,As thanks for saving me, I brought \Nyou to the mansion,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.83,0:23:27.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and now...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.53,0:23:30.59,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,Still, thank you so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.72,0:23:33.72,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! It's fine, it's fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.72,0:23:35.56,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I only did it because I wanted to...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.95,0:23:38.24,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you'd say that,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.24,0:23:40.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it doesn't make me feel any better.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.90,0:23:42.69,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,I must do something to thank you...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.98,0:23:46.10,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. Then, I'll take you up on that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.09,0:23:49.48,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Go on a date with me, Emilia-tan!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.48,0:23:50.53,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,A "date"?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.11,0:23:54.23,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,We'll go out together, see the same things,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.23,0:23:56.31,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,eat the same things, do the same things,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.31,0:23:58.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and share the same memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.12,0:24:01.12,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,And that's all you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.12,0:24:03.23,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,That's exactly what I want.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.23,0:24:05.87,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,I want to show you off to the village kids,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.87,0:24:08.02,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,and there's this awesome flower field!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.02,0:24:12.50,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Even if all we do is stroll around, \Nit'd be a special occasion to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.92,0:24:20.74,Default,Emilia,0000,0000,0000,,All right. I'll go on a date with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.74,0:24:27.32,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! That's why you're my EMF!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.32,0:24:32.36,Default,Subaru,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, "EMF" stands for "Emilia-tan, major fairy"!
